pages.title: Big diplomatic win for India, Masood Azhar declared international terrorist as China lifts hold
pages.description: Home Photos DNA/WION was the first to break the news. Siddhant Sibal May 1, 2019, 06:41 PM IST In a major diplomatic victory for India, the man behind several terror attacks in the country including Pulwama terror attack, Masood Azhar has finally been listed as an international terrorist by the United Nation security council's 1267 committee. China earlier on Wednesday removed its hold on the listing of Masood Azhar, the chief of Pakistan based and united nations listed terror group.

pages.title: PM Modi's Efforts Led To UN Ban On Masood Azhar, Says Amit Shah
pages.description: New Delhi: Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) president Amit Shah has hailed Prime Minister Narendra Modi after the United Nations (UN) designated terror organisation Jaish-e-Mohammad's chief Masood Azhar a global terrorist and asserted that this is why 'India needs a strong and decisive leader'. 'That is why India needs a strong & decisive leader. Grateful to PM Narendra Modi and his diplomatic efforts that led to the UN designating Masood Azhar as a global terrorist. It was long over due.
